          \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Described as 'calcare' by Manganaro, a fine plaque  missing the upper right and lower right corners, and with the surviving upper right portion broken but still connecting.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.limestone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html\">limestone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003C!--Manganaro-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">46\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">55\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">3\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.damaged\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>seven lines of large fine Latin letters, lines 1-2 larger and central (all lines centred), with the final line reduced and less regular (due to lack of space).\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Several of the letter T are taller than other letters; use of apices and interpuncts.\u003C/p>\u003C!-- measurements from Manganaro -->\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Line 1-2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"65\" atMost=\"65\">65\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line3\" to=\"line4\">Line 3-4\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"55\" atMost=\"55\">55\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line5\" to=\"line6\">Line 5-6\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"40\" atMost=\"40\">40\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line7\" to=\"line7\">Line 7\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"25\" atMost=\"25\">25\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270\">Catina\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2525068\">Catania\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.49223, 15.07041\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0001\" notAfter-custom=\"0100\">1st century CE\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1960\">Recovered c.1960 in course of construction of S. Bambino hospital (so Manganaro)\u003Cgeo>37.5060446,15.0809441\u003C/geo>\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- hospital location -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"not-observed\" subtype=\"lost\">Lost? The piece was described by Manganaro 1989 as being in the Museo Civico Castel Ursino, but neither Korhonen not the EpiCUM project have located it there; some inscriptions in this group have since been located in the storage of the Catania Parco Archeologico in the ex-manifattura tabacchi, but not this one and we have so far been unable to locate it.\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs a